### IKEA Hack: Make a Couch into a Coffee Table

IKEA has a lot of great furniture, but their so-called "coffee table" designs are actually very poor substitutes.  They are cheaply made and don't fit the purpose of a coffee table at all.  They are also very low to the ground which makes them hard to use for anything other than standing on.  If you want to upgrade your coffee table but can't afford an actual coffee table, you can make one out of a cheap IKEA couch.


### Materials:

* A cheap IKEA couch
* A drill
* A hammer
* A level
* Wood glue
* A drill bit that is the same diameter as the holes in the couch
* A screw gun and screws
* A drill bit that is the same diameter as the screws
* A flat surface to drill and screw the table to


### Directions:
1. Drill holes in the flat surface that are the same diameter as the screws that will attach the table to the surface.  The holes should be about 1/2 inch from the edge of the surface.
2. Drill holes in the top of the couch that are the same diameter as the drill bit that you will use to screw the table together.  The holes should be about 1/2 inch from the edge of the couch.

4. Drill pilot holes in the table and couch so the screws will go through the table and into the couch.  Use the level to ensure the holes are straight and the screws are going into the same place.  Use the screw gun to install the screws.  The screws should go into the couch and into the table so the table can be removed from the couch.
